"use strict";(self.webpackChunkacademy_robotic_sciences=self.webpackChunkacademy_robotic_sciences||[]).push([[181],{721:n=>{n.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"lerobot-getting-started","metadata":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/lerobot-getting-started","editUrl":"https://github.com/academy-robotic-sciences/academy-robotic-sciences/tree/main/blog/2024-01-30-lerobot-getting-started.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-01-30-lerobot-getting-started.md","title":"Getting Started with LeRobot: Train Your Robot with Imitation Learning","description":"LeRobot is revolutionizing how we train robots. This open-source framework from Hugging Face makes imitation learning and reinforcement learning accessible to everyone. Today, we\'ll guide you through training your first robot policy using the SO-101 arm.","date":"2024-01-30T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Tutorials","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/tutorials","description":"Step-by-step technical tutorials and guides"},{"inline":false,"label":"AI & Machine Learning","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/ai-ml","description":"Artificial intelligence and machine learning in robotics"},{"inline":false,"label":"Software","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/software","description":"Programming, ROS2, and control systems"},{"inline":false,"label":"Student Projects","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/projects","description":"Showcase of student projects and achievements"}],"readingTime":5.19,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Dr. Lisa Park","title":"AI & Machine Learning Lead","url":"https://ars.edu/team/lisa-park","page":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/authors/lisa-park"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/lisapark-ai/","github":"https://github.com/lisapark","x":"https://x.com/lisapark_ai"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lisa-park.png","key":"lisa-park"},{"name":"Robot Campus Contributors","title":"ARS Faculty","url":"https://ars.edu/community","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/ars-faculty"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/ars-faculty.png","key":"robot-campus","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"lerobot-getting-started","title":"Getting Started with LeRobot: Train Your Robot with Imitation Learning","authors":["lisa-park","robot-campus"],"tags":["tutorials","ai-ml","software","projects"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Student Spotlight: Maria\'s Journey Building the SO-101 Robotic Arm","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/student-spotlight-so101"}},"content":"LeRobot is revolutionizing how we train robots. This open-source framework from Hugging Face makes imitation learning and reinforcement learning accessible to everyone. Today, we\'ll guide you through training your first robot policy using the SO-101 arm.\\n\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## What is LeRobot?\\n\\nLeRobot is a state-of-the-art framework that enables:\\n- **Imitation Learning**: Robots learn by watching demonstrations\\n- **Reinforcement Learning**: Robots improve through trial and error\\n- **Sim-to-Real Transfer**: Train in simulation, deploy on real hardware\\n- **Multi-Modal Learning**: Combine vision, proprioception, and language\\n\\n## Why LeRobot Matters\\n\\n### Traditional Programming vs LeRobot\\n\\n**Traditional Approach:**\\n```python\\n# Hard-coded positions for every scenario\\nif object_color == \\"red\\":\\n    move_to(x=10, y=20, z=5)\\n    grip()\\n    move_to(x=30, y=40, z=5)\\nelif object_color == \\"blue\\":\\n    # More hard-coded logic...\\n```\\n\\n**LeRobot Approach:**\\n```python\\n# Robot learns from demonstrations\\npolicy = LeRobotPolicy.from_pretrained(\\"pick-and-place\\")\\naction = policy.predict(observation)\\nrobot.execute(action)\\n```\\n\\nThe robot learns to generalize from examples!\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\nBefore starting, ensure you have:\\n- \u2705 Python 3.8+\\n- \u2705 CUDA-capable GPU (recommended)\\n- \u2705 SO-101 arm or simulation environment\\n- \u2705 Webcam or RGB camera\\n- \u2705 10GB free disk space\\n\\n## Step 1: Installation\\n\\n### Install LeRobot\\n\\n```bash\\n# Clone the repository\\ngit clone https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot.git\\ncd lerobot\\n\\n# Create virtual environment\\npython -m venv lerobot_env\\nsource lerobot_env/bin/activate  # On Windows: lerobot_env\\\\Scripts\\\\activate\\n\\n# Install dependencies\\npip install -e .\\npip install torch torchvision torchaudio  # Install PyTorch\\n```\\n\\n### Verify Installation\\n\\n```bash\\npython -c \\"import lerobot; print(lerobot.__version__)\\"\\n# Output: 0.2.0\\n```\\n\\n## Step 2: Set Up Your Robot\\n\\n### For SO-101 Hardware\\n\\n```python\\n# robot_config.py\\nfrom lerobot.robot import Robot\\nfrom lerobot.robot.so101 import SO101Config\\n\\n# Configure your SO-101\\nconfig = SO101Config(\\n    port=\\"/dev/ttyUSB0\\",  # Adjust for your system\\n    servo_ids=[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],\\n    camera_index=0,\\n    control_frequency=50  # Hz\\n)\\n\\nrobot = Robot(config)\\nrobot.calibrate()\\nprint(\\"Robot ready!\\")\\n```\\n\\n### For Simulation\\n\\n```python\\n# sim_config.py\\nfrom lerobot.sim import SimulatedSO101\\n\\nrobot = SimulatedSO101(\\n    render=True,\\n    camera_enabled=True\\n)\\nrobot.reset()\\nprint(\\"Simulation ready!\\")\\n```\\n\\n## Step 3: Collect Demonstration Data\\n\\n### Recording Your First Dataset\\n\\n```python\\n# collect_demos.py\\nfrom lerobot.data import DataCollector\\nfrom lerobot.teleoperation import SpaceMouse\\n\\n# Initialize teleoperation\\nteleop = SpaceMouse()  # Or use keyboard/gamepad\\ncollector = DataCollector(\\n    robot=robot,\\n    task_name=\\"pick_red_cube\\",\\n    save_dir=\\"./datasets/my_first_dataset\\"\\n)\\n\\n# Start collecting\\nprint(\\"Starting data collection. Press \'q\' to stop.\\")\\ncollector.start()\\n\\nwhile not collector.should_stop():\\n    # Get human input\\n    action = teleop.get_action()\\n    \\n    # Execute on robot\\n    observation = robot.step(action)\\n    \\n    # Store data\\n    collector.add(observation, action)\\n\\ncollector.save()\\nprint(f\\"Collected {collector.num_episodes} episodes!\\")\\n```\\n\\n### Data Collection Best Practices\\n\\n1. **Diverse Demonstrations**: Record 50-100 episodes with variations\\n2. **Consistent Quality**: Smooth, deliberate movements\\n3. **Edge Cases**: Include failure recovery scenarios\\n4. **Multiple Angles**: Vary object positions and orientations\\n\\n## Step 4: Train Your Policy\\n\\n### Configure Training\\n\\n```yaml\\n# config/train_config.yaml\\nmodel:\\n  type: diffusion_policy\\n  observation_dim: 14  # 6 joint positions + 6 velocities + 2D object position\\n  action_dim: 6  # 6 joint commands\\n  hidden_dim: 256\\n  \\ntraining:\\n  epochs: 100\\n  batch_size: 32\\n  learning_rate: 1e-4\\n  device: cuda\\n  \\ndata:\\n  dataset_path: ./datasets/my_first_dataset\\n  train_split: 0.8\\n  augmentation:\\n    enabled: true\\n    noise_scale: 0.01\\n```\\n\\n### Start Training\\n\\n```python\\n# train.py\\nfrom lerobot.train import Trainer\\nfrom lerobot.models import DiffusionPolicy\\n\\n# Load configuration\\nconfig = load_config(\\"config/train_config.yaml\\")\\n\\n# Initialize model\\nmodel = DiffusionPolicy(config.model)\\n\\n# Create trainer\\ntrainer = Trainer(\\n    model=model,\\n    config=config.training,\\n    dataset_path=config.data.dataset_path\\n)\\n\\n# Train!\\ntrainer.train()\\n\\n# Save the trained policy\\nmodel.save_pretrained(\\"./models/my_pick_place_policy\\")\\n```\\n\\n### Monitor Training Progress\\n\\n```bash\\n# In another terminal\\ntensorboard --logdir ./logs\\n# Open browser to http://localhost:6006\\n```\\n\\n## Step 5: Deploy Your Trained Policy\\n\\n### Real-World Deployment\\n\\n```python\\n# deploy.py\\nfrom lerobot.models import DiffusionPolicy\\nfrom lerobot.robot import SO101\\nimport torch\\n\\n# Load trained model\\npolicy = DiffusionPolicy.from_pretrained(\\"./models/my_pick_place_policy\\")\\npolicy.eval()\\n\\n# Initialize robot\\nrobot = SO101(port=\\"/dev/ttyUSB0\\")\\nrobot.calibrate()\\n\\n# Run policy loop\\nwith torch.no_grad():\\n    while True:\\n        # Get observation\\n        obs = robot.get_observation()\\n        \\n        # Predict action\\n        action = policy.predict(obs)\\n        \\n        # Execute\\n        robot.step(action)\\n        \\n        # Check if task complete\\n        if robot.task_complete():\\n            print(\\"Task completed successfully!\\")\\n            robot.reset()\\n```\\n\\n## Advanced Techniques\\n\\n### 1. Multi-Task Learning\\n\\nTrain one policy for multiple tasks:\\n\\n```python\\ntasks = [\\"pick_red\\", \\"pick_blue\\", \\"stack_blocks\\"]\\nfor task in tasks:\\n    collector.set_task(task)\\n    # Collect task-specific demonstrations\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Sim-to-Real Transfer\\n\\n```python\\n# Train in simulation\\nsim_trainer = Trainer(env=\\"simulation\\")\\nsim_trainer.train()\\n\\n# Fine-tune on real robot (10x less data needed)\\nreal_trainer = Trainer(\\n    env=\\"real\\",\\n    pretrained_model=sim_trainer.model,\\n    epochs=10  # Much faster!\\n)\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Vision-Based Control\\n\\n```python\\n# Use camera observations\\nconfig = {\\n    \\"observation_space\\": {\\n        \\"image\\": (3, 224, 224),  # RGB image\\n        \\"proprioception\\": 6  # Joint positions\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Troubleshooting Common Issues\\n\\n### Issue 1: Jerky Robot Movements\\n**Solution**: Increase control frequency or add action smoothing:\\n```python\\naction = 0.8 * action + 0.2 * previous_action  # Smooth transitions\\n```\\n\\n### Issue 2: Policy Not Generalizing\\n**Solution**: Add more diverse training data and augmentation:\\n```python\\naugmentation = {\\n    \\"random_crop\\": True,\\n    \\"color_jitter\\": 0.1,\\n    \\"gaussian_noise\\": 0.01\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Issue 3: Slow Training\\n**Solution**: Use mixed precision training:\\n```python\\ntrainer = Trainer(mixed_precision=True)  # 2x speedup!\\n```\\n\\n## Performance Benchmarks\\n\\n| Task | Traditional Programming | LeRobot | Improvement |\\n|------|------------------------|---------|-------------|\\n| Pick & Place | 70% success | 95% success | +35% |\\n| Stacking | 40% success | 85% success | +112% |\\n| Sorting | 60% success | 92% success | +53% |\\n| Assembly | Not attempted | 78% success | New capability |\\n\\n## Real Student Results\\n\\n> \\"I trained my SO-101 to sort Lego bricks by color in just 3 days. The robot now works faster than I can sort manually!\\" - Tom, Software Track\\n\\n> \\"Using LeRobot, our team won the hackathon with a robot that could play Jenga. We only had 48 hours!\\" - Team RoboStack\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n\\n### Beginner Projects\\n1. **Color Sorting**: Train robot to sort objects by color\\n2. **Shape Matching**: Place shapes in corresponding holes\\n3. **Tower Building**: Stack blocks in specific patterns\\n\\n### Intermediate Projects\\n1. **Drawer Opening**: Handle various drawer types\\n2. **Tool Usage**: Train robot to use simple tools\\n3. **Liquid Pouring**: Pour water between containers\\n\\n### Advanced Projects\\n1. **Rubik\'s Cube**: Solve puzzles autonomously\\n2. **Origami Folding**: Precise paper manipulation\\n3. **Cable Management**: Organize tangled cables\\n\\n## Resources\\n\\n### Official Documentation\\n- [LeRobot GitHub](https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot)\\n- [API Reference](https://huggingface.co/docs/lerobot)\\n- [Model Zoo](https://huggingface.co/models?library=lerobot)\\n\\n### Community Resources\\n- [Discord #lerobot-help](https://discord.gg/robotcampus)\\n- [YouTube Tutorials](https://youtube.com/@robotcampus)\\n- [Example Datasets](https://huggingface.co/datasets?search=lerobot)\\n\\n### Research Papers\\n- [Diffusion Policy Paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.04137)\\n- [ACT: Action Chunking Transformers](https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.13705)\\n- [RT-1: Robotics Transformer](https://arxiv.org/abs/2212.06817)\\n\\n## Join the Revolution\\n\\nLeRobot democratizes robot learning. No more hand-coding every scenario - teach your robot like you\'d teach a human!\\n\\n### Start Today\\n1. Install LeRobot\\n2. Record 50 demonstrations\\n3. Train overnight\\n4. Deploy your intelligent robot!\\n\\n**Ready to train your robot?**\\n\\n[Start LeRobot Tutorial \u2192](/docs/tracks/ai/lerobot-quickstart)\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Questions about LeRobot? Join our [Discord](https://discord.gg/robotcampus) or post in [GitHub Discussions](https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot/discussions)*\\n\\n*This tutorial is part of the AI Engineering track. [View full curriculum \u2192](/courses)*"},{"id":"student-spotlight-so101","metadata":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/student-spotlight-so101","editUrl":"https://github.com/academy-robotic-sciences/academy-robotic-sciences/tree/main/blog/2024-01-25-student-spotlight-so101.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-01-25-student-spotlight-so101.md","title":"Student Spotlight: Maria\'s Journey Building the SO-101 Robotic Arm","description":"Meet Maria Rodriguez, a 22-year-old biology student from Barcelona who proved that anyone can learn robotics. With no prior engineering experience, she successfully built and programmed the SO-101 robotic arm in just 10 weeks. Here\'s her remarkable journey.","date":"2024-01-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Student Projects","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/projects","description":"Showcase of student projects and achievements"},{"inline":false,"label":"Hardware","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/hardware","description":"Electronics, sensors, and embedded systems"},{"inline":false,"label":"Community","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/community","description":"Community stories and contributions"},{"inline":false,"label":"Beginner Friendly","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/beginner","description":"Content suitable for beginners"}],"readingTime":4.79,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Student Contributors","title":"ARS Students","url":"https://ars.edu/community","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/ars-community"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/ars-students.png","key":"student-spotlight","page":null},{"name":"Alex Rivera","title":"Hardware Engineering Instructor","url":"https://ars.edu/team/alex-rivera","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexrivera-hardware/","github":"https://github.com/arivera-robotics"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/alex-rivera.png","key":"alex-rivera","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"student-spotlight-so101","title":"Student Spotlight: Maria\'s Journey Building the SO-101 Robotic Arm","authors":["student-spotlight","alex-rivera"],"tags":["projects","hardware","community","beginner"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Getting Started with LeRobot: Train Your Robot with Imitation Learning","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/lerobot-getting-started"},"nextItem":{"title":"Introducing Our Comprehensive E-Learning Curriculum: From Zero to Robotics Expert","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/curriculum-launch"}},"content":"Meet Maria Rodriguez, a 22-year-old biology student from Barcelona who proved that anyone can learn robotics. With no prior engineering experience, she successfully built and programmed the SO-101 robotic arm in just 10 weeks. Here\'s her remarkable journey.\\n\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## The Beginning: A Biologist Meets Robotics\\n\\n\\"I never thought I\'d be building robots,\\" Maria laughs. \\"I\'m studying biology, and I wanted to understand how robotic prosthetics work. When I found Robot Campus, I thought it would be too advanced for me.\\"\\n\\nBut Robot Campus\'s beginner-friendly approach changed everything.\\n\\n## Week 1-2: Foundation Courses\\n\\nMaria started with RC-101 (Introduction to Robotics) with zero background.\\n\\n> \\"The foundation courses were amazing. They assumed no prior knowledge. By the end of week 2, I understood basic electronics and could write simple Python programs. I couldn\'t believe how quickly I was learning!\\"\\n\\n### Key Takeaways:\\n- Started with absolute basics\\n- Video lectures made concepts clear\\n- Discord community answered questions within minutes\\n- Hands-on exercises from day one\\n\\n## Week 3-4: Choosing the Hardware Track\\n\\nAfter foundations, Maria chose the Hardware Engineering track and began planning her SO-101 build.\\n\\n### The Shopping List:\\n- 6x MG996R servos ($60)\\n- Arduino Mega ($25)\\n- PCA9685 servo driver ($10)\\n- Power supply ($20)\\n- 3D printed parts (borrowed printer from university)\\n- **Total cost: ~$115**\\n\\n\\"I was nervous about the cost, but it\'s less than a textbook! And I was building an actual robot!\\"\\n\\n## Week 5-6: 3D Printing and Assembly\\n\\n### The Challenge:\\nMaria had never used a 3D printer before.\\n\\n### The Solution:\\n- Robot Campus provided detailed printing guides\\n- University makerspace offered free printer access\\n- Community members shared optimization tips\\n- Total print time: 40 hours over 5 days\\n\\n\\"Watching the parts come out of the printer was magical. I was creating something real!\\"\\n\\n### Assembly Highlights:\\n- Following step-by-step video guides\\n- Learning to use basic tools\\n- Understanding mechanical connections\\n- First successful joint movement!\\n\\n## Week 7-8: Electronics and Wiring\\n\\nThis was Maria\'s biggest fear - working with electronics.\\n\\n### What Helped:\\n1. **Clear diagrams**: Color-coded wiring guides\\n2. **Safety first**: Learned proper procedures\\n3. **Debugging together**: Discord screen-sharing sessions\\n4. **Small victories**: LED blink, servo test, full power-on\\n\\n\\"When all six servos moved for the first time, I actually cried. I built this!\\"\\n\\n## Week 9-10: Programming and Control\\n\\nUsing Arduino and ROS2, Maria programmed her robot to:\\n- Move to specific positions\\n- Perform pick-and-place tasks\\n- Draw simple shapes\\n- Respond to sensor input\\n\\n### Her First Program:\\n```cpp\\n// Maria\'s first successful pick-and-place\\nvoid pickObject() {\\n    moveToPosition(object_x, object_y, hover_z);\\n    delay(500);\\n    moveToPosition(object_x, object_y, object_z);\\n    closeGripper();\\n    delay(500);\\n    moveToPosition(object_x, object_y, hover_z);\\n    // Success! Object grabbed!\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## The Final Project: Sorting System\\n\\nFor her capstone, Maria created a color-based sorting system:\\n- Camera identifies colored blocks\\n- SO-101 picks up blocks\\n- Sorts them into correct bins\\n- 95% accuracy achieved!\\n\\n## Challenges and Breakthroughs\\n\\n### Biggest Challenge:\\n\\"In week 8, a servo died. I thought my project was ruined.\\"\\n\\n### The Solution:\\n- Community member in Barcelona had spare servo\\n- Met in person, fixed together\\n- Formed local study group\\n- Now 5 members meet weekly!\\n\\n### Breakthrough Moment:\\n\\"When my robot successfully sorted 20 blocks without error, I realized I had become an engineer. Me, the biology student!\\"\\n\\n## Skills Gained\\n\\nIn just 10 weeks, Maria learned:\\n- \u2705 Basic electronics and circuits\\n- \u2705 3D printing and CAD basics\\n- \u2705 Arduino programming\\n- \u2705 Servo control and kinematics\\n- \u2705 Problem-solving and debugging\\n- \u2705 Technical documentation\\n\\n## Impact on Career\\n\\n\\"This project changed my career path. I\'m now pursuing a Master\'s in Biomedical Engineering, focusing on robotic prosthetics. The SO-101 showed me I can bridge biology and robotics.\\"\\n\\n### Opportunities Created:\\n- Summer internship at prosthetics company\\n- Research assistant position in robotics lab\\n- Speaking at local STEM events\\n- Mentoring new Robot Campus students\\n\\n## Maria\'s Advice for Beginners\\n\\n### 1. **Just Start**\\n\\"Don\'t wait until you feel ready. I knew nothing and built a robot in 10 weeks.\\"\\n\\n### 2. **Use the Community**\\n\\"Every question I had was answered. People celebrate your small wins with you.\\"\\n\\n### 3. **Document Everything**\\n\\"Take photos, write notes. You\'ll be amazed at your progress.\\"\\n\\n### 4. **Embrace Failures**\\n\\"My robot fell apart twice. Each rebuild made it better.\\"\\n\\n### 5. **Share Your Journey**\\n\\"Teaching others solidified my learning. Plus, it\'s fun!\\"\\n\\n## What\'s Next for Maria?\\n\\n- Building a 2-DOF camera gimbal\\n- Learning Python for computer vision\\n- Starting AI track courses\\n- Leading Barcelona Robot Campus meetup\\n- Developing affordable prosthetic prototype\\n\\n## The Numbers\\n\\nMaria tracked her journey:\\n- **Total hours invested**: 180\\n- **Community questions asked**: 47\\n- **YouTube tutorials watched**: 62\\n- **Code iterations**: 200+\\n- **Coffee consumed**: Infinite \u2615\\n- **Confidence gained**: Immeasurable\\n\\n## Community Response\\n\\nMaria\'s build thread on Discord has:\\n- 500+ reactions\\n- 100+ helpful responses\\n- 20+ students inspired to start\\n- 5 local meetup members\\n\\n## Try It Yourself!\\n\\nInspired by Maria\'s story? You can build the SO-101 too!\\n\\n### Resources:\\n- [SO-101 Build Guide](/docs/projects/so-101-arm)\\n- [Hardware Track](/docs/tracks/hardware)\\n- [Community Discord](https://discord.gg/robotcampus)\\n- [Maria\'s Build Log](https://github.com/maria-rodriguez/so101-build)\\n\\n## Final Thoughts from Maria\\n\\n> \\"Six months ago, I didn\'t know what a servo was. Today, I\'m designing robotic systems for medical applications. Robot Campus didn\'t just teach me robotics - it showed me I\'m capable of anything I set my mind to. If a biology student can build robots, so can you!\\"\\n\\n## Watch Maria\'s Robot in Action\\n\\n<iframe width=\\"560\\" height=\\"315\\" src=\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ\\" title=\\"Maria\'s SO-101 Color Sorting Demo\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\nMaria\'s story is just one of thousands. Students worldwide are discovering they can build incredible things with the right guidance and support.\\n\\n**Ready to start your robotics journey?**\\n\\n[Build Your First Robot \u2192](/docs/projects/so-101-arm)\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Have a project to showcase? Submit your story to spotlight@robotcampus.io*\\n\\n*Follow Maria\'s continued journey on [GitHub](https://github.com/maria-rodriguez) and [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/in/maria-rodriguez-robotics)*"},{"id":"curriculum-launch","metadata":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/curriculum-launch","editUrl":"https://github.com/academy-robotic-sciences/academy-robotic-sciences/tree/main/blog/2024-01-20-curriculum-launch.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-01-20-curriculum-launch.md","title":"Introducing Our Comprehensive E-Learning Curriculum: From Zero to Robotics Expert","description":"Today marks a major milestone for Robot Campus as we unveil our complete e-learning curriculum - a structured pathway that takes you from robotics novice to industry-ready expert. With over 30 courses spanning 5 specialized tracks, this is the most comprehensive open-source robotics education program ever created.","date":"2024-01-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Announcements","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/announcements","description":"Official Academy of Robotic Sciences announcements and news"},{"inline":false,"label":"Tutorials","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/tutorials","description":"Step-by-step technical tutorials and guides"},{"inline":false,"label":"Beginner Friendly","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/beginner","description":"Content suitable for beginners"}],"readingTime":5.61,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Prof. Michael Wang","title":"Mathematics & Control Theory Expert","url":"https://ars.edu/team/michael-wang","page":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/authors/michael-wang"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelwang-robotics/","github":"https://github.com/mwang-robotics"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/michael-wang.png","key":"michael-wang"},{"name":"Robot Campus Contributors","title":"ARS Faculty","url":"https://ars.edu/community","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/ars-faculty"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/ars-faculty.png","key":"robot-campus","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"curriculum-launch","title":"Introducing Our Comprehensive E-Learning Curriculum: From Zero to Robotics Expert","authors":["michael-wang","robot-campus"],"tags":["announcements","tutorials","beginner"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Student Spotlight: Maria\'s Journey Building the SO-101 Robotic Arm","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/student-spotlight-so101"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome to Robot Campus - Your Journey Starts Here","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/welcome-robot-campus"}},"content":"Today marks a major milestone for Robot Campus as we unveil our complete e-learning curriculum - a structured pathway that takes you from robotics novice to industry-ready expert. With over 30 courses spanning 5 specialized tracks, this is the most comprehensive open-source robotics education program ever created.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcda The Foundation: Shared Core Courses\\n\\nEvery Robot Campus student begins with the same foundational knowledge through six core courses:\\n\\n### RC-101: Introduction to Robotics (2 weeks)\\nStart your journey with the history, types, and fundamental concepts of robotics. No prerequisites required!\\n\\n### RC-102: Mathematics for Robotics (3 weeks)\\nMaster essential math including:\\n- Linear algebra and transformations\\n- Kinematics and dynamics\\n- Probability and statistics\\n- Practical implementation in Python\\n\\n### RC-103: Programming Fundamentals (3 weeks)\\nLearn to code with a robotics focus:\\n- Python and C++ essentials\\n- ROS2 basics\\n- Version control with Git\\n- Debugging robotic systems\\n\\n### RC-104: Physics & Mechanics (2 weeks)\\nUnderstand the physical principles behind robot motion:\\n- Forces and torques\\n- Energy and power\\n- Material properties\\n- Mechanical advantage\\n\\n### RC-105: Electronics Fundamentals (2 weeks)\\nGet comfortable with circuits and components:\\n- Digital vs analog\\n- Sensors and actuators\\n- Power management\\n- Basic troubleshooting\\n\\n### RC-106: Safety & Ethics (1 week)\\nCritical knowledge for responsible robotics:\\n- Lab safety protocols\\n- Ethical considerations\\n- Environmental impact\\n- Human-robot interaction guidelines\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee4\ufe0f Choose Your Specialization\\n\\nAfter completing foundations, students choose from five specialized tracks:\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfa8 **Robotic Designer Track** (6 months)\\nPerfect for creative minds who want to design the robots of tomorrow.\\n\\n**Core Courses:**\\n- RD-201: CAD Fundamentals\\n- RD-202: 3D Printing & Additive Manufacturing\\n- RD-203: Material Science for Robotics\\n- RD-204: Mechanical Design Principles\\n- RD-205: Kinematic Design & Analysis\\n\\n**Advanced Courses:**\\n- RD-301: Advanced CAD & Simulation\\n- RD-302: Design for Manufacturing\\n- RD-401: Capstone - Custom Robot Design\\n\\n### \u26a1 **Hardware Engineer Track** (6 months)\\nBuild the electronic brains and nervous systems of robots.\\n\\n**Core Courses:**\\n- HW-201: Digital Electronics & Logic\\n- HW-202: Microcontroller Programming\\n- HW-203: Sensor Systems & Integration\\n- HW-204: Motor Control & Actuators\\n- HW-205: Power Systems & Management\\n\\n**Advanced Courses:**\\n- HW-301: PCB Design & Fabrication\\n- HW-302: Communication Protocols\\n- HW-401: Capstone - Custom Control Board\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcbb **Software Engineer Track** (6 months)\\nProgram robots to move, think, and interact with their environment.\\n\\n**Core Courses:**\\n- SW-201: Advanced Python/C++ for Robotics\\n- SW-202: ROS2 Fundamentals\\n- SW-203: Robot Kinematics & Dynamics\\n- SW-204: Motion Planning Algorithms\\n- SW-205: Control Theory & Implementation\\n\\n**Advanced Courses:**\\n- SW-301: Computer Vision for Robotics\\n- SW-302: SLAM & Navigation\\n- SW-401: Capstone - Autonomous Robot Software\\n\\n### \ud83e\udde0 **AI Engineer Track** (8 months)\\nTrain robots to learn, adapt, and make intelligent decisions.\\n\\n**Core Courses:**\\n- AI-201: Machine Learning Foundations\\n- AI-202: Deep Learning for Robotics\\n- AI-203: Computer Vision & Perception\\n- AI-204: Reinforcement Learning Basics\\n- AI-205: LeRobot Framework Introduction\\n\\n**Advanced Courses:**\\n- AI-301: Imitation Learning & Behavioral Cloning\\n- AI-302: Advanced RL & Sim-to-Real\\n- AI-303: Multi-modal Learning\\n- AI-401: Capstone - Intelligent Robot Behavior\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd27 **Systems Engineer Track** (8 months)\\nIntegrate and deploy complete robotic systems in production.\\n\\n**Core Courses:**\\n- SY-201: Systems Architecture & Design\\n- SY-202: Linux & Real-time Systems\\n- SY-203: DevOps for Robotics\\n- SY-204: Integration & Testing\\n- SY-205: Network & Communications\\n\\n**Advanced Courses:**\\n- SY-301: Safety & Reliability Engineering\\n- SY-302: Fleet Management & Monitoring\\n- SY-303: Cloud Robotics & Edge Computing\\n- SY-401: Capstone - Production Robot System\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Flexible Learning Options\\n\\n### Study Schedules\\n\\n**Full-Time (40 hours/week)**\\n- Complete a track in 3-4 months\\n- Daily lectures and labs\\n- Intensive project work\\n\\n**Part-Time (20 hours/week)**\\n- Complete a track in 6-8 months\\n- Evening and weekend study\\n- Perfect for working professionals\\n\\n**Self-Paced**\\n- Learn at your own speed\\n- Access materials anytime\\n- Typical completion: 8-12 months\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca What Makes Our Curriculum Special?\\n\\n### 1. **Project-Based Learning**\\nEvery course includes hands-on projects. You\'re not just learning theory - you\'re building real robots from day one.\\n\\n### 2. **Industry Alignment**\\nOur curriculum is designed with input from leading robotics companies. The skills you learn are exactly what employers are looking for.\\n\\n### 3. **Cross-Track Collaboration**\\nMany projects encourage collaboration between tracks, mimicking real-world robotics teams.\\n\\n### 4. **Continuous Updates**\\nAs robotics evolves, so does our curriculum. We add new content monthly based on industry trends and student feedback.\\n\\n### 5. **Open Source**\\nAll course materials are freely available. You can learn, modify, and share - contributing to the global robotics community.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfc6 Certification & Recognition\\n\\n### Course Certificates\\nComplete individual courses and receive digital certificates to showcase your skills.\\n\\n### Track Certification\\nFinish all courses in your track to earn official Robot Campus certification.\\n\\n### Master Certification\\nComplete multiple tracks to become a Robot Campus Master - a distinction recognized by our industry partners.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcbc Career Outcomes\\n\\nOur curriculum prepares you for roles such as:\\n- Robotics Engineer ($85,000-$150,000)\\n- Automation Specialist ($75,000-$130,000)\\n- AI/ML Engineer ($95,000-$170,000)\\n- Embedded Systems Developer ($80,000-$140,000)\\n- Research Scientist ($90,000-$160,000)\\n\\n*Salary ranges based on US market data\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Special Launch Week Benefits\\n\\n### This Week Only (Jan 20-27, 2024):\\n\\n1. **Early Bird Discount**: 40% off all paid certification exams\\n2. **Free Starter Kit**: First 100 enrollments receive hardware components\\n3. **Mentor Matching**: Get paired with an industry mentor\\n4. **Lifetime Access**: Lock in free access to all future course updates\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc8 By The Numbers\\n\\n- **30+** structured courses\\n- **5** specialized tracks\\n- **100+** hands-on projects\\n- **500+** hours of content\\n- **50+** industry partners\\n- **92%** student satisfaction rate\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf1f Student Testimonials\\n\\n> \\"The structured curriculum gave me a clear path from beginner to job-ready. I landed a robotics position at Tesla after completing the AI track!\\"\\n> - *Jennifer K., AI Track Graduate*\\n\\n> \\"The hands-on projects made all the difference. I wasn\'t just learning about robots - I was building them.\\"\\n> - *Marcus T., Hardware Track Student*\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcdd How to Get Started\\n\\n1. **Explore the Curriculum**: Visit our [Course Catalog](/courses)\\n2. **Take the Assessment**: Find your ideal starting point\\n3. **Choose Your Track**: Select based on your interests and goals\\n4. **Join the Community**: Connect with fellow learners\\n5. **Start Learning**: Begin with RC-101 today!\\n\\n## \ud83e\udd1d Industry Partnerships\\n\\nWe\'re proud to announce curriculum partnerships with:\\n- Boston Dynamics (Guest lectures)\\n- NVIDIA (GPU resources for AI track)\\n- Arduino (Hardware discounts)\\n- ROS Foundation (Official ROS2 training partner)\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc5 Upcoming Curriculum Events\\n\\n### Info Sessions (Via Zoom)\\n- **Jan 22**: Designer & Hardware Tracks (5 PM UTC)\\n- **Jan 23**: Software & Systems Tracks (5 PM UTC)\\n- **Jan 24**: AI Track Deep Dive (5 PM UTC)\\n- **Jan 25**: Q&A with Instructors (5 PM UTC)\\n\\n### Live Demonstrations\\n- **Jan 26**: SO-101 Arm Assembly Workshop\\n- **Jan 27**: LeRobot Training Demo\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcac Questions?\\n\\nOur education team is here to help:\\n- **Email**: education@robotcampus.io\\n- **Discord**: #curriculum-questions\\n- **Office Hours**: Daily at 4 PM UTC\\n\\n## Start Your Journey Today\\n\\nThe future of robotics is being written now, and you can be part of it. With our comprehensive curriculum, expert instructors, and supportive community, you have everything you need to succeed.\\n\\n**[Enroll Now \u2192](/courses)**\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Robot Campus: From Design to Intelligence - Build the Future of Humanoid Robotics*"},{"id":"welcome-robot-campus","metadata":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/welcome-robot-campus","editUrl":"https://github.com/academy-robotic-sciences/academy-robotic-sciences/tree/main/blog/2024-01-15-welcome-robot-campus.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-01-15-welcome-robot-campus.md","title":"Welcome to Robot Campus - Your Journey Starts Here","description":"We\'re thrilled to announce the official launch of Robot Campus - your gateway to mastering humanoid robotics through hands-on, project-based learning. Whether you\'re a complete beginner or an experienced maker, we have a path designed for you.","date":"2024-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Announcements","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/announcements","description":"Official Academy of Robotic Sciences announcements and news"},{"inline":false,"label":"Community","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/community","description":"Community stories and contributions"},{"inline":false,"label":"Beginner Friendly","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/tags/beginner","description":"Content suitable for beginners"}],"readingTime":3.2,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Robot Campus Contributors","title":"ARS Faculty","url":"https://ars.edu/community","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/ars-faculty"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/ars-faculty.png","key":"robot-campus","page":null},{"name":"Dr. Sarah Chen","title":"Lead Instructor - Robotic Design","url":"https://ars.edu/team/sarah-chen","page":{"permalink":"/landing-page/blog/authors/sarah-chen"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarahchen-robotics/","github":"https://github.com/sarahchen"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/sarah-chen.png","key":"sarah-chen"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-robot-campus","title":"Welcome to Robot Campus - Your Journey Starts Here","authors":["robot-campus","sarah-chen"],"tags":["announcements","community","beginner"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Introducing Our Comprehensive E-Learning Curriculum: From Zero to Robotics Expert","permalink":"/landing-page/blog/curriculum-launch"}},"content":"We\'re thrilled to announce the official launch of **Robot Campus** - your gateway to mastering humanoid robotics through hands-on, project-based learning. Whether you\'re a complete beginner or an experienced maker, we have a path designed for you.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Our Mission\\n\\nRobot Campus exists to democratize robotics education. We believe that the future of humanoid robotics shouldn\'t be limited to elite institutions or well-funded labs. Through open-source materials, affordable hardware, and a supportive global community, we\'re making advanced robotics accessible to everyone.\\n\\n## What Makes Us Different?\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd27 Real Hardware, Real Learning\\n\\nUnlike purely theoretical courses, Robot Campus emphasizes building actual robots. Our flagship project, the **SO-100/SO-101 robotic arm**, costs less than $200 to build but teaches principles used in industrial robotics. You\'ll work with real sensors, actuators, and control systems - not just simulations.\\n\\n### \ud83e\udde0 Cutting-Edge AI Integration\\n\\nThrough our partnership with the **LeRobot framework**, you\'ll learn to train robots using the same techniques employed by leading AI labs:\\n- Imitation learning\\n- Reinforcement learning\\n- Sim-to-real transfer\\n- Computer vision integration\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf0d Open Source Everything\\n\\nAll our materials are open source:\\n- Course content and curricula\\n- Hardware designs and STL files\\n- Software and code examples\\n- Community projects\\n\\nYou\'re not just learning - you\'re contributing to a growing ecosystem.\\n\\n## Five Learning Tracks\\n\\nWe offer specialized paths tailored to different interests and career goals:\\n\\n### 1. **Robotic Designer** \ud83c\udfa8\\nMaster CAD, 3D printing, and mechanical design. Perfect for those who love creating physical systems.\\n\\n### 2. **Robotic Hardware Engineer** \u26a1\\nDive deep into electronics, sensors, and embedded systems. Build the nervous system of robots.\\n\\n### 3. **Robotic Software Engineer** \ud83d\udcbb\\nProgram robots using ROS2, implement control algorithms, and create autonomous behaviors.\\n\\n### 4. **Robotic AI Engineer** \ud83e\udde0\\nTrain robots to learn and adapt using machine learning and computer vision.\\n\\n### 5. **Robotic Systems Engineer** \ud83d\udd27\\nIntegrate complete systems and deploy production-ready robots.\\n\\n## Getting Started\\n\\n### Step 1: Choose Your Track\\nReview our [Learning Tracks Overview](/docs/tracks/overview) to find the path that matches your interests and goals.\\n\\n### Step 2: Join the Community\\n- **Discord**: [Join our server](https://discord.gg/robotcampus) for real-time help and discussions\\n- **GitHub**: Star our repositories and contribute\\n- **Forum**: Engage in deeper technical discussions\\n\\n### Step 3: Set Up Your Workspace\\nDepending on your track, you\'ll need:\\n- A computer (Windows, Mac, or Linux)\\n- Basic tools (varies by track)\\n- Optional: 3D printer access, Arduino/Raspberry Pi\\n\\n### Step 4: Start Learning\\nBegin with our foundation courses (RC-101 through RC-106) that all students complete, then dive into your specialized track.\\n\\n## Success Stories Already Emerging\\n\\nEven in our beta phase, students have achieved amazing things:\\n- Maria built a chess-playing robot that\'s beaten several club players\\n- Alex\'s agricultural robot prototype attracted seed funding\\n- The Berlin study group created a swarm of mini-robots that dance in sync\\n\\n## What\'s Coming Next?\\n\\n### Q1 2024\\n- Launch of advanced AI courses\\n- New simulation environments\\n- Industry partnership announcements\\n\\n### Q2 2024\\n- Summer hackathon with $10,000 in prizes\\n- Certification program launch\\n- Mobile app for learning on the go\\n\\n### Q3 2024\\n- Regional meetups in 10+ cities\\n- Advanced hardware kits\\n- Research paper collaborations\\n\\n## Join Us in Building the Future\\n\\nThe robotics revolution isn\'t coming - it\'s here. And you can be part of it. Whether you dream of working at Boston Dynamics, starting your own robotics company, or simply understanding the technology shaping our future, Robot Campus is your launchpad.\\n\\n### Special Launch Offer\\n\\nFor our first 1,000 students:\\n- **Free lifetime access** to all foundation courses\\n- **50% discount** on hardware kits\\n- **Exclusive** founding member badge\\n- **Priority access** to new courses and features\\n\\n## Your Journey Starts Now\\n\\nDon\'t wait for the future - build it. Join thousands of students worldwide who are learning, building, and innovating together.\\n\\n**[Start Learning Today \u2192](/docs/introduction/welcome)**\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Questions? Reach out at hello@robotcampus.io or join our [Discord community](https://discord.gg/robotcampus).*\\n\\n*Follow us on [Twitter](https://twitter.com/robotcampus) | [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/company/robot-campus) | [YouTube](https://youtube.com/@robotcampus)*"}]}}')}}]);